item.title: Analysis of Birth Data: Implications for Maternal Healthcare
item.description: Outline: This project involves a comprehensive analysis of a dataset from a maternity hospital, containing information on 250 single births, with variables like birth weight, gestational weeks, maternal age, and binary indicators for low birth weight, preterm birth, hypertension, and baby gender. The main objective is to explore the connections between birth weight and these variables. The report will begin with an introduction defining the research scope, followed by descriptive statistics to characterize the data.
